nodes.title: About
widgets_values:
This workflow utilises ControlNet OpenPose model and area composition to achieve character interaction with separate prompts for each character at a high consistency.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                             WORKFLOW MODES
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

This workflow features 2 modes, you can select the mode by changing the values of the black node near the bottom of the [Global Settings/Loaders] group. There are:

1) Input Mode: 
The image you provide will be applied to the generation for guidance
Image dimensions set in [Global Settings/Loaders] will be overridden by the dimensions of the provided image
You can either input an OpenPose image or an unprocessed image from which a pose will be extracted. Depending on which it is, set the correct value in the switch at the bottom of [Global Settings/Loaders]

2) Generate Mode:
The workflow will first generate an image in [Area & Pose]
   This will use dimensions specified in [Global Settings/Loaders]
   This will only use the {Pose & Background} prompt (cyan)
   This will use the checkpoint and VAE specified in [Area & Pose]
The resulting image will be passed through ControlNet OpenPose Preprocessor to extract the pose
 (The above is only to generate the pose image)
Afterwards, the proper image generation will begin using the usual settings from [Global Settings/Loaders] and prompt areas set in [Area & Pose]. The pose image will be used for guidance.

Notes:
 - In Input Mode, an image will still be generated in [Area & Pose] but the resulting OpenPose image will not be used. This is a problem with ComfyUI or WAS's logic switches and circumventing it would require an additional switch in an awkward spot which I opted not to make as things are complicated enough already. Generation time will be slightly prolonged because of this.
 - In Generate Mode a separate checkpoint is used as different checkpoints have a varied knowledge of poses, letting you use the pose knowledge from one checkpoint and then for the proper generation switch to another one that has a more preferable art style for instance
 - In Generate Mode it may be preferable to use a realistic model as the OpenPose preprocessor has an easier time detecting poses in realistic characters
 - In Generate Mode, you can enable/disable the detection of body, hands and facial features in the {Openpose Preprocessor} node
 - Don't get dissuaded by Openpose Preprocessor finding only one character. Oftentimes 2 characters will be generated in the proper generation anyways. I'm not exactly sure why it works, but I think it can be due to cropping of the OpenPose image before applying it to the subject conditionings, which makes the AI think those are 2 separate characters.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        SUBJECT AREAS AND PREVIEW
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - Specify subject dimensions and locations in [Area & Pose]. The set areas will be visualized in the [Subject Visualization] image preview once image generation has reached a certain point. Some area overlap is desired, especially with close interactions
  - Subject 1 will be marked in blue
  - Subject 2 will be marked in green

 - In Input Mode, the overall initial image dimensions are ovewritten by those of the provided image, but areas still have to be set manually
 - In Generate Mode, where the characters appear is not under control so it's best to keep the framing such that the characters occupy most of the space to ensure that conditioning areas are properly located
 - Ideally, the visualization would appear as soon as possible to give feedback o whether the areas are set correctly, but the features necessary to force this order in generation are not yet implemented in ComfyUI

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                PROMPTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - The quality preset selected at the top of PROMPT will be added at the beginning of both subject prompts. The selector has a step of 0.5, but the value is rounded down, so 1.5 will choose the preset with the number 1 and so on
- The Pose & Background prompt has a separate quality prompt that is used in pose image generation in Generate Mode (because you can use a different checkpoint here). For the proper generation, the above-selected preset is used.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       GENERATING A SINGLE SUBJECT
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Generating a single subject is not very efficient as you'll still have to either input an image in Input mode or generate a new one in Generate mode but it is possible

 - To do so, leave both subject prompts blank and use only the background prompt
 - In Generate mode it will allow you to create a pose with one checkpoint and the rest with another, so there is a slight versatility advantage over a normal generation. You'll also be able to save the pose by right-clicking the first preview image

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                 OTHER
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - Black nodes are switches that enable/disable certain functions and switch between certain options (eg. upscaling using latent upscale vs an upscale model)

 - The black VAE reroute near [Global Settings/Loaders] is connected to all relevant nodes besides those in [Area & Pose]
 - The black VAE reroute in [Area & Pose] is connected to all relevant nodes in [Area & Pose]

 - With 2 faces, face restoration will run twice, once for each face, potentially significantly prolonging generation time. Just a heads up.

- Grid Size for this workflow is 25

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                 ADJUSTING CONDITIONING VISUALISATION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

This section is mainly intended for those who struggle to see the subject areas in the [Conditioning Visualisation].

The colours of each subject's area visualization can be adjusted with the RGB values in the {Visualize Subject 1} and {Visualize Subject 2} nodes in the bottom-right of [Area & Pose]

The opacity of the subject areas can be adjusted with the (blend_percentage) setting in {Areas Over Image} in the bottom-right of [Area & Pose]
